<TITLE> CID gets 4 days to grill ex-NSI man Liakat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 28 (bdnews24.com)A Chittagong court on Thursday gave the CID four days to question former NSI deputy director (technical) retired major Liakat Hossain in the sensational 10-truck arms haul case. Chittagong Additional Metropolitan Sessions Judge M Asaduzzaman granted the remand following an appeal by investigation officer for the case, SSP Moniruzzaman Chowdhury, to remand him for five days on Wednesday. He said that the confessional statement of Shahabuddin also linked Liakat to the arms case. Liakat was picked up from his Dhanmondi residence on Tuesday and brought to Chittagong on Wednesday afternoon for interrogation. Police seized ten trucks loaded with arms and ammunition at the secured jetty of Chittagong Urea Fertiliser Ltd on the midnight of Apr 1, 2004. bdnews
